author: newsroom@capegazette.com (Staff)
title: Cape JV football falls to Central 24-10
text:
Cape JV football falls to Central 24-10 Oct 15, 2015 Photo by: Dan Cook Cape sophomore Parker Savage drags a Sussex Central tackler on a kickoff return. 
The Cape JV football squad fell to 1-3 with a 24-10 loss to Sussex Central Oct. 12 at Legends Stadium. 
Scoring for the Vikings came on a fumble recovery by Jermaine Willis, who took it to the end zone and then tacked on the two-point conversion. Zack Dale tackled the Golden Knights' quarterback in the end zone for a safety for the other Vikings score. Cape JV quarterback Nolan Brown looks for a receiver in the Vikings' 24-10 loss to the Knights. (Photo by: Dan Cook) Vikings linebacker Jermaine Willis knocks Central running back Tynez Warner to the turf. (Photo by: Dan Cook) After Liam Zolper causes a Golden Knights fumble, Jermaine Willis scoops it up and runs in for a Vikings touchdown. (Photo by: Dan Cook) Junior varsity linebacker Liam Zolper, right, pulls down a Sussex Central ball carrier. (Photo by: Dan Cook) Cape sophomore James McMullin takes down Central ball carrier Jaron Curtis. (Photo by: Dan Cook)
